            "description": "Non-planar two-loop four-point diagram contributing to muon-electron scattering ($\\mu e \\to \\mu e$) in $D = 6 - 2\\varepsilon$ dimensions, finite in that dimension. Contains muon lines of mass $M$, electron lines of mass $m$ (with $M/m \\sim 200$), and three photon (massless) propagators. Evaluated at a phase space point close to that of DiVita et al. [1806.08241] but including the electron mass, up to $\\varepsilon^4$ with $N=10^8$. The kinematic configuration is exceptional (generalized permutahedron not guaranteed) but feyntrop still converges; numbers verified against AMFlow and pySecDec.",
